{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.8",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 8 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:1",
      "text": "Then Baldad the Sauchite answered, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:2",
      "text": "How long wilt thou speak these things, how long shall the breath of thy mouth be abundant in words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:3",
      "text": "Will the Lord be unjust when he judges; or will he that has made all things pervert justice?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:4",
      "text": "If thy sons have sinned before him, he has cast them away because of their transgression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:5",
      "text": "But be thou early in prayer to the Lord Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:6",
      "text": "If thou art pure and true, he will hearken to thy supplication, and will restore to thee the habitation of righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:7",
      "text": "Though then thy beginning should be small, yet thy end should be unspeakably great.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:8",
      "text": "For ask of the former generation, and search diligently among the race of our fathers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:9",
      "text": "(for we are of yesterday, and know nothing; for our life upon the earth is a shadow:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:10",
      "text": "shall not these teach thee, and report to thee, and bring out words from their heart?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:11",
      "text": "Does the rush flourish without water, or shall the flag grow up without moisture?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:12",
      "text": "When it is yet on the root, and though it has not been cut down, does not any herb wither before it has received moisture?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:13",
      "text": "Thus then shall be the end of all that forget the Lord: for the hope of the ungodly shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:14",
      "text": "For his house shall be without inhabitants, and his tent shall prove a spider’s web.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:15",
      "text": "If he should prop up his house, it shall not stand: and when he has taken hold of it, it shall not remain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:16",
      "text": "For it is moist under the sun, and his branch shall come forth out of his dung-heap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:17",
      "text": "He lies down upon a gathering of stones, and shall live in the mist of flints.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:18",
      "text": "If God should destroy him, his place shall deny him. Hast thou not seen such things,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:19",
      "text": "that such is the overthrow of the ungodly? and out of the earth another shall grow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:20",
      "text": "For the Lord will by no means reject the harmless man; but he will not receive any gift of the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:21",
      "text": "But he will fill with laughter the mouth of the sincere, and their lips with thanksgiving.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.8.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:22",
      "text": "But their adversaries shall clothe themselves with shame; and the habitation of the ungodly shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
